<sec id="id-8628785e-300d-4fb5-e9a7-98ae8fbaf8d7" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:tbx="urn:iso:std:iso:30042:ed-1" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"><title><bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="e6b4d5e5-fee7-442e-9e21-fe30bd747d9c" timestamp="1671534344500"?>General principles<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="e6b4d5e5-fee7-442e-9e21-fe30bd747d9c"?></bold></title><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="b9e9fb94-bedc-4a36-94b2-c92c5dc9e9ab" timestamp="1671534352895"?>When it comes to setting up a GBV grievance mechanism it is particularly important to acknowledge the barriers to reporting. Culture and context often hinder survivors/victims from reporting but also fear of retaliation, which makes the victim/survivor-based approach the most important feature of a GBV grievance mechanism, it is therefore highly important to have several channels of reporting such as (but not limited to) in-person reporting, digital, anonymous etc.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="b9e9fb94-bedc-4a36-94b2-c92c5dc9e9ab"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="e3ad8848-1bd6-4e80-ee24-cd2c5c374aa9" timestamp="1671534352895"?>Some of the key principles which provide an effective grievance mechanism are<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="e3ad8848-1bd6-4e80-ee24-cd2c5c374aa9"?></p><list list-type="dash"><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="d392592d-b928-463f-a5a1-28ac1a234b03" timestamp="1671534352895"?><list-item id="id-5b1de11f-9288-48e8-bbf1-a6adbef53f2a"><p>transparency,</p></list-item><list-item id="id-636d5998-5cb8-4e8e-a630-4d64330e901b"><p>impartiality,</p></list-item><list-item id="id-78af5f56-d26f-4d48-c8e0-37ef3ca492da"><p>confidentiality,</p></list-item><list-item id="id-02a151a9-5898-49a1-b93d-efd182a474c9"><p>accessibility and/or predictability (timely/clear time frame),</p></list-item><list-item id="id-ef835736-8ba4-4a3f-94f0-c10f03a254ef"><p>legitimacy,</p></list-item><list-item id="id-24bdaab3-3096-4456-9393-be178369009f"><p>equity.</p></list-item><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="d392592d-b928-463f-a5a1-28ac1a234b03"?></list><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="20ae3a30-3be0-4aca-ad93-7fb044424f85" timestamp="1671534352895"?>When it comes to setting up a grievance mechanism some organizations suggest separating the function for internal grievances and those that are external.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="20ae3a30-3be0-4aca-ad93-7fb044424f85"?></p></sec>